line-height:150%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"m=
argin:0;">Pretty quickly I discovered that there are plenty of Democrats wh=
o would agree with
the essence of what my Moscow source told me=E2=80=94though they aren=E2=80=
=99t willing to say so openly. All Friday afternoon, as the Zelensky disast=
er metastasized, I received texts from staunch supporters of Ukraine who we=
re disgusted with Trump and Vance=E2=80=99s behavior, but felt that the Ukr=
ainian president had indeed bungled the meeting. Zelensky =E2=80=9Cfucked t=
his up so badly,=E2=80=9D one prominent Ukraine supporter texted. =E2=80=9C=
Zelensky stepped in it,=E2=80=9D wrote another.<br/><br/>Ever since the Ova=
l debacle, pro-Ukraine liberals
have subscribed to the talking point that Zelensky was ambushed and the con=
frontation was planned by the Trump team in advance. But in conversation af=
ter conversation this weekend, transatlanticist Democrats who have been lea=
ding this town=E2=80=99s charge on Ukraine all expressed doubt that the eve=
nt was anything other than a trap of Zelensky=E2=80=99s own making.<br/><br=
/>After all, <em>he</em> was the one who lobbied to come to Washington to s=
ign the minerals deal=E2=80=94which many of them think was a mistake to
begin with (why feed the lion?)=E2=80=94and then rose to Vance=E2=80=99s co=
ndescending scolding. =E2=80=9CHe took the bait,=E2=80=9D the prominent Ukr=
aine supporter moaned. Trump, and especially Vance, acted like disappointed=
-not-angry school principals, dressing down the president of a war-torn cou=
ntry as if he were a schoolboy.<br/><br/>But if he wanted the meeting, Zele=
nsky should have expected this=E2=80=94and been prepared to deal with Trump=
 and Vance accordingly. =E2=80=9CMy sense is it wasn=E2=80=99t Trump=E2=80=
=99s plan,=E2=80=9D one former senior
<strong>Biden</strong> official told me. =E2=80=9CFor me, it didn=E2=80=99t=
 feel like it was Vance=E2=80=99s plan either. Vance just flips out. It has=
 less to do with Ukraine politics and more to do with the fact that Trump m=
akes them all fight for his attention and his respect. And for Vance, Zelen=
sky and Ukraine are low-hanging fruit.=E2=80=9D (Asked for comment, a White=
 House spokesperson referred to <a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJl=
bWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dWWHBDOHFiVlNDampOUVVETlcwTT0iLCJocmV=
mIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly94LmNvbS9TaGVsYnlUYWxjb3R0L3N0YXR1cy8xODk1NTU0ODM0NDMxOTAxOT=
